08/11/2006
ZAGREB, Croatia -- President Stipe Mesic met with visiting Cypriot counterpart Tassos Papadopoulos on Tuesday (November 7th). He assured Mesic that Cyprus fully backs Croatia's bid for EU membership. They agreed that bilateral economic and trade relations need a boost and that co-operation in tourism, construction, shipbuilding, maritime affairs, education and culture offer strong potential. 
Also Tuesday, Croatian Foreign and EU Integration Minister Kolinda Grabar-Kitarovic began a three-day visit to the Russian Federation. She counterpart Sergei Lavrov discussed ways to boost institutional and economic collaboration. (Vjesnik, Phileleftheros - 08/11/06; HRT, HINA, CNA - 07/11/06)
